SIMPLE: scramble
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Scramble
<hw>Scram"ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Scrambled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Scrambling</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Freq.
of Prov. E. <ets>scramb</ets> to rake together with the hands, or of
<ets>scramp</ets> to snatch at. cf. <er>Scrabble</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To clamber with hands and knees; to scrabble; <as>as,
to <ex>scramble</ex> up a cliff; to <ex>scramble</ex> over the
rocks</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To struggle eagerly with others for something thrown
upon the ground; to go down upon all fours to seize something; to catch
rudely at what is desired.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Of other care they little reckoning make,⟦br⟧
Than how to <qex>scramble</qex> at the shearer's feast.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scramble</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Scramble
<hw>Scram"ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
collect by scrambling; <as>as, to <ex>scramble</ex> up
wealth</as>.</def> <rj><au>Marlowe.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To prepare (eggs) as a dish for the table, by
stirring the yolks and whites together while cooking.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scramble</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Scramble
<hw>Scram"ble</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of
scrambling, climbing on all fours, or clambering.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The act of jostling and pushing for something
desired; eager and unceremonious struggle for what is thrown or held
out; <as>as, a <ex>scramble</ex> for office</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Scarcity [of money] enhances its price, and increases the
<qex>scramble</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Locke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scrambled eggs</ent>⟦br⟧
